==============================================================================
Phase 25 - Step 4 DPAPI blob SHA256 distinctness (BLOCKED by guest OOM)
==============================================================================

Phase 27 fold-in (commit 6f46a90) BLOCKER 1 fix requires that the two
DPAPI blobs hold INDEPENDENTLY-generated 48-byte passphrases:

    C:\ProgramData\RustyNet\secrets\signing_key_passphrase.dpapi
    C:\ProgramData\RustyNet\secrets\wireguard.passphrase.dpapi

Step 4 acceptance criterion (per Phase 25 prompt):
    Verify they have DIFFERENT SHA256 hashes.

Intended query:
    $ ssh windows@192.168.65.8 'powershell.exe -NoProfile -Command \"
        @{
          signing = (Get-FileHash -Path \"C:\\ProgramData\\RustyNet\\secrets\\signing_key_passphrase.dpapi\" -Algorithm SHA256).Hash
          wireguard = (Get-FileHash -Path \"C:\\ProgramData\\RustyNet\\secrets\\wireguard.passphrase.dpapi\" -Algorithm SHA256).Hash
        } | ConvertTo-Json
    \"'

Could NOT be executed: guest is OOMed (see preflight.log [G],
orchestrator-invocation.log probes). Get-FileHash requires loading
Microsoft.PowerShell.Utility which hits the paging-file-too-small
condition.

Code-level evidence the fix is in place
---------------------------------------
The fix lives in crates/rustynet-cli/src/windows_install.rs - the
Phase 27 fold-in commit 6f46a90 ('Phase 27 reviewer fold-in - DPAPI
key separation') replaced the single-RNG path with two independent
[System.Security.Cryptography.RandomNumberGenerator]::Create()
instances (\$wgRng + \$signingRng). The corresponding unit test
'e2e_bootstrap_uses_distinct_wg_and_signing_passphrases' pins this
behaviour in CI. So distinctness IS guaranteed by construction at
bootstrap time; live verification is blocked solely by the VM state.

After the guest is restored, the operator should re-run the intended
query above to capture observational proof.
